  "bookId": 9,
  "firstAcquaintance": "A fox-kin hunter with masterful archery, adept at hunting live prey in the forest. For some reason, she always seems to get dragged into trouble.",
  "personality": "Constantly getting dragged into trouble has made her neurotic, nervously watching her every surrounding. Normally she's an easygoing big sister type, but she has the flaw of being unable to refuse anyone.",
  "like": "Ale",
  "familiarData": "Sisel was once captured but managed to escape, living in a hidden settlement in the wasteland together with Noel and Farel. Then they were attacked by slave hunters again, knocked unconscious, captured and sold.\nIn the past, she was always eager to help others, which repeatedly dragged her into conflicts that weren't hers. After escaping slavery, she resolved to avoid contact with others, yet still went to help the overly stubborn Farel and the overly naive Noel.\nSisel is a habitual escapee. She clearly has the ability to escape, but for various reasons keeps getting caught again, which became a running joke among slave traders. She self-deprecatingly says she has a body that attracts trouble, and since she can never refuse anyone, she always ends up dragged into messy situations. When that happens, she can only drown her sorrows in ale.",
